            <fr:title text="Relative Boolean algebra">Relative Boolean algebra</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>-algebra. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is a <html:em><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>-Boolean algebra</html:em>, if for all prime ideals <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>, in the following <fr:link href="/idem-comm-V39C/" title="Orthogonal factorisation: (pro-open, t-conservative)" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-V39C/" display-uri="idem-comm-V39C" type="local">factorisation</fr:link>
  
  <html:figure><fr:resource hash="40b524655ed757eeb57eba684f4d642c"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/40b524655ed757eeb57eba684f4d642c.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
    \begin {tikzcd}
      D \ar [d, two heads] \ar [r] & E \ar [d, two heads] \\ 
      f^{-1}(I)/D \ar [r] & I/E
    \end {tikzcd}
  ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:figure>

  the factor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(I)/D \to  I/E]]></fr:tex> is an <html:em><fr:link href="/idem-comm-VEWK/" title="Epimorphisms between distributive lattices" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-VEWK/" display-uri="idem-comm-VEWK" type="local">epimorphism</fr:link></html:em>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
